    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Some Remarks on $φ$-Dedekind rings and $φ$-Prufer rings
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Zhang%2C+X">Xiaolei Zhang</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Qi%2C+W">Wei Qi</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08278v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;-von <span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span> regular rings, nonnil-Notherian rings and nonnil-coherent rings are given. We finally characterize $φ$-Dedekind rings and $φ$-\Prufer\ rings in terms of $φ$-flat modules, nonnil-injective modules and nonnil-FP-injective modules.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08278v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.08278v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08278v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        In this paper, the notions of nonnil-injective modules and nonnil-FP-injective modules are introduced and studied. Especially, we show that a $φ$-ring $R$ is an integral domain if and only if any nonnil-injective (resp., nonnil-FP-injective) module $R$-module is injective (resp., FP-injective). Some new characterizations of $φ$-von <span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span> regular rings, nonnil-Notherian rings and nonnil-coherent rings are given. We finally characterize $φ$-Dedekind rings and $φ$-\Prufer\ rings in terms of $φ$-flat modules, nonnil-injective modules and nonnil-FP-injective modules.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08278v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.08278v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
