    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        The norm attainment problem for functions of projections
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=B%C3%B6ttcher%2C+A">Albrecht Böttcher</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Spitkovsky%2C+I+M">Ilya M. Spitkovsky</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.06213v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        The paper is concerned with the problem of identifying the norm attaining operators in the von <span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span> algebra generated by two orthogonal projections on a Hilbert space. This algebra contains every skew projection on that Hilbert space and hence the results of the paper also describe functions of skew projections and their adjoints that attain the norm.
        
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.06213v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
