    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        A metric characterization of freeness
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Cadilhac%2C+L">Léonard Cadilhac</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Collins%2C+B">Benoit Collins</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.02944v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;be a finite von <span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span> algebra and $u_1,\dots,u_N$ be unitaries in $\mathcal{M}$. We show that $u_1,\dots,u_N$ freely generate $L(\mathbb{F}_N)$ if and only if $$\left\|\sum_{i=1}^N u_i \otimes (u_i^{\mathrm{op}})^* + u_i^*\otimes u_i^{\mathrm{op}}\right\|_{\mathcal{M}\overline{\otimes}\mathcal{M}^{\mathrm{op}}} = 2\sqrt{2N - 1}.$$
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.02944v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.02944v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.02944v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        Let $\mathcal{M}$ be a finite von <span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span> algebra and $u_1,\dots,u_N$ be unitaries in $\mathcal{M}$. We show that $u_1,\dots,u_N$ freely generate $L(\mathbb{F}_N)$ if and only if $$\left\|\sum_{i=1}^N u_i \otimes (u_i^{\mathrm{op}})^* + u_i^*\otimes u_i^{\mathrm{op}}\right\|_{\mathcal{M}\overline{\otimes}\mathcal{M}^{\mathrm{op}}} = 2\sqrt{2N - 1}.$$
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.02944v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.02944v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 4 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
    </p>
    
