    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Theoretical and numerical study of the decay in a viscoelastic Bresse System
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Hassan%2C+J">Jamilu Hassan</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Messaoudi%2C+S">Salim Messaoudi</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Arwadi%2C+T">Toufic Arwadi</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Hindi%2C+M">Mohammad Hindi</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2102.12590v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        In this paper, we consider a one-dimensional finite-memory Bresse system with homogeneous Dirichlet-<span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span>-<span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span> boundary conditions. We prove some general decay results for the energy associated with the system in the case of equal and non-equal speeds of wave propagation under appropriate conditions on the relaxat&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2102.12590v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2102.12590v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2102.12590v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        In this paper, we consider a one-dimensional finite-memory Bresse system with homogeneous Dirichlet-<span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span>-<span class="search-hit mathjax">Neumann</span> boundary conditions. We prove some general decay results for the energy associated with the system in the case of equal and non-equal speeds of wave propagation under appropriate conditions on the relaxation function. In addition, we show by giving an example that in the case of equal speeds of wave propagation and for certain polynomially decaying relaxation functions, our result gives an optimal decay rate in the sense that the decay rate of the system is exactly the same as that of the relaxation function considered.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2102.12590v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2102.12590v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
